## CSS Styles for FlowSection Component

All FlowSection-related CSS styles are defined in `/Users/ia/Documents/code/@orgs/my-entourage/entourage-web/src/app/globals.css`.

### FlowSection-Specific Classes

#### 1. `.flow-action-badge` (Lines 201-203)
**Purpose**: Animated color-shifting glow effect for floating action badges (Extract, Organize)

```css
.flow-action-badge {
  animation: flow-action-glow 4s ease-in-out infinite;
}
```

**Usage in Component**:
- Line 180: Desktop "Extract" badge (top-left)
- Line 184: Desktop "Organize" badge (bottom-right)
- Line 322: Mobile "Extract" badge (top-left)
- Line 326: Mobile "Organize" badge (bottom-right)

#### 2. `.flow-action-badge` Dark Mode Variant (Lines 224-226)

```css
.dark .flow-action-badge {
  animation: flow-action-glow-dark 4s ease-in-out infinite;
}
```

---

#### 3. `.flow-task-arrive` (Lines 248-251)
**Purpose**: Pulsing box-shadow animation for the "Your Tasks" arrival badge

```css
.flow-task-arrive {
  will-change: box-shadow;
  animation: flow-task-pulse 4s ease-out infinite;
}
```

**Usage in Component**:
- Line 196: Desktop "Your Tasks" container
- Line 338: Mobile "Your Tasks" container

---

#### 4. `.flow-checkmark-bounce` (Lines 265-268)
**Purpose**: Bouncing scale animation for the checkmark icon inside the task arrival badge

```css
.flow-checkmark-bounce {
  will-change: transform;
  animation: flow-checkmark-bounce 4s ease-out infinite;
}
```

**Usage in Component**:
- Line 199: Desktop checkmark container (emerald background)
- Line 341: Mobile checkmark container (emerald background)

---

### Animation Keyframes

#### 1. `@keyframes flow-action-glow` (Lines 205-222)
**Purpose**: Light mode color-cycling glow for action badges (amber → violet → emerald)

```css
@keyframes flow-action-glow {
  0%, 100% {
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 0 transparent;
    border-color: rgb(228 228 231); /* zinc-200 */
  }
  25% {
    box-shadow: 0 0 8px 0 rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.4);
    border-color: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.6);
  }
  50% {
    box-shadow: 0 0 8px 0 rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.4);
    border-color: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.6);
  }
  75% {
    box-shadow: 0 0 8px 0 rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.4);
    border-color: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.6);
  }
}
```

**Colors Used**:
- 25%: Amber (#F59E0B / rgba(245, 158, 11))
- 50%: Violet (#8B5CF6 / rgba(139, 92, 246))
- 75%: Emerald (#10B981 / rgba(16, 185, 129))

---

#### 2. `@keyframes flow-action-glow-dark` (Lines 228-245)
**Purpose**: Dark mode variant with reduced opacity for color-cycling glow

```css
@keyframes flow-action-glow-dark {
  0%, 100% {
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 0 transparent;
    border-color: rgb(63 63 70); /* zinc-700 */
  }
  25% {
    box-shadow: 0 0 8px 0 rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.3);
    border-color: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.5);
  }
  50% {
    box-shadow: 0 0 8px 0 rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.3);
    border-color: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.5);
  }
  75% {
    box-shadow: 0 0 8px 0 rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.3);
    border-color: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.5);
  }
}
```

**Differences from Light Mode**:
- Lower opacity (0.3 vs 0.4 for box-shadow, 0.5 vs 0.6 for border)
- Different base border color (zinc-700 vs zinc-200)

---

#### 3. `@keyframes flow-task-pulse` (Lines 253-263)
**Purpose**: Expanding pulse effect (emerald glow) for task arrival badge

```css
@keyframes flow-task-pulse {
  0%, 70% {
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 0 transparent;
  }
  75% {
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 0 rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.5);
  }
  100% {
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 12px rgba(16, 185, 129, 0);
  }
}
```

**Animation Pattern**:
- 0-70%: No shadow
- 75%: Emerald shadow appears
- 75-100%: Shadow expands to 12px and fades out

---

#### 4. `@keyframes flow-checkmark-bounce` (Lines 270-283)
**Purpose**: Bouncing scale effect for checkmark icon

```css
@keyframes flow-checkmark-bounce {
  0%, 70% {
    transform: scale(1);
  }
  80% {
    transform: scale(1.25);
  }
  90% {
    transform: scale(0.95);
  }
  100% {
    transform: scale(1);
  }
}
```

**Animation Pattern**:
- 0-70%: Normal size
- 80%: Scale up to 125%
- 90%: Scale down to 95% (bounce effect)
- 100%: Return to normal size

---

### Related Animations (Circuit Board Signals)

The FlowSection also uses circuit board signal animations defined in the same file:

#### `.circuit-signal` (Lines 114-121)
**Purpose**: Base class for animated signal dots moving along SVG paths

```css
.circuit-signal {
  offset-anchor: 8px 0px;
  animation: circuit-signal-path;
  animation-iteration-count: infinite;
  animation-timing-function: cubic-bezier(0.75, -0.01, 0, 0.99);
  animation-duration: 4s;
  animation-delay: 1.5s;
}
```

#### Individual Signal Paths (Lines 123-181)
Ten signal variants (`.circuit-signal-1` through `.circuit-signal-10`) with different SVG paths and timing:

- Each has unique `offset-path` (SVG path)
- Different `animation-delay` (1.5s to 2.5s)
- Different `animation-duration` (3s to 5s)

#### `@keyframes circuit-signal-path` (Lines 183-198)
**Purpose**: Controls signal movement and opacity along the path

```css
@keyframes circuit-signal-path {
  0% {
    offset-distance: 0%;
    opacity: 0;
  }
  10% {
    opacity: 1;
  }
  85% {
    opacity: 1;
  }
  100% {
    offset-distance: 100%;
    opacity: 0;
  }
}
```

---

### Summary

**File**: `/Users/ia/Documents/code/@orgs/my-entourage/entourage-web/src/app/globals.css`

**FlowSection Animation Classes**:
- `.flow-action-badge` (line 201) + dark variant (line 224)
- `.flow-task-arrive` (line 248)
- `.flow-checkmark-bounce` (line 265)

**FlowSection Animation Keyframes**:
- `@keyframes flow-action-glow` (line 205) - 4s color-cycling glow
- `@keyframes flow-action-glow-dark` (line 228) - Dark mode variant
- `@keyframes flow-task-pulse` (line 253) - 4s expanding pulse
- `@keyframes flow-checkmark-bounce` (line 270) - 4s bounce effect

**Related Circuit Animations**:
- `.circuit-signal` + variants (lines 114-181)
- `@keyframes circuit-signal-path` (line 183)

All animations are GPU-optimized using `will-change` properties where applicable.

